==English==
===Etymology===
a portmanteau word with [[chuckle]] and [[snort]]. First used in the poem ''Jabberwocky'' by Lewis Carroll.
===Noun===
'''chortle'''
# A [[joyful]] [[laugh]], rather like a [[snort]]ing [[chuckle]].
===Intransitive verb===
'''chortle'''
# To laugh in the manner of a chortle.
#* 'O frabjous day! Callooh! Callay!' He '''chortled''' in his joy.
===Synonyms===
*[[chuckle]]
*[[giggle]]